        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 5:08PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 508 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
southwestern Colorado Springs, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Colorado Springs, Fountain, Air Force Academy, Manitou Springs,
Stratmoor, Fort Carson, Security, Falcon, Cimarron Hills, Peterson
Space Force Base, Gleneagle, and Security-Widefield.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
